<br>
My jaw dropped to floor when I saw what I could do now.  My pet now hits all the time in the 40s and mobs often miss my pet (summoned plate, etc.).  I can DoT a mob for 600 hp at the beginning and then get a 650+ focused SoS off a little later.  The damage dealing capacity of the mage once it hits 44 is amazing.<br>
<br>
What sums it up best was when I was in Rathe Mountains last night.  I was camping up on the hill just killing any giant that moved (obviously, not the ones taken).  It was pathetic how easy it was-- getting exp and plat.  The best was when I received a tell from one of the druids who was up there root-dotting the giants.  The quote was, &quot;OMG, your a mage?!?&quot; right after I dropped 2 giants right in from of him.<br>
<br>
Mages are so cool.  I thought I would just share my extreme happiness with everyone.<br>
<br>
Good hunting!<br>
<br>
casala, lvl 44 (almost 45) mage of Saryn<br>
<br>
